						               													<description>Played in a Shibumi board,the game tries to emulate the Tetris experience, combining it the elegance and aesthetics of Shibumi.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a given player's turn, he must put one of his pre-set groups of marbles (every group has a specific shape/pattern) respecting the following conditions below:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 &amp;ndash; The original form of the group must be preserved&amp;#10;2 &amp;ndash; Each ball of the group must occupy (and fit) a single space, being in the first floor, or stacked.&amp;#10;3 &amp;ndash; All balls of a group must be entirely supported.&amp;#10;4 &amp;ndash; The player can&amp;rsquo;t use the same group pattern that his opponent used in his last move.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal is to be the player with the least number of groups in hand or, given a tie in the first condition, the least number or marbles in hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Haikai&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Falling leaf&amp;#10;dances under the full moon.&amp;#10;search for a place to rest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
